Packaging browse-sqlite3 for Distributions
==========================================

This file is for distribution packagers who want to add browse-sqlite3
to their distro's package repository.  Template packaging files for
several systems are provided under dist/.  Each is roughly 90% complete
-- the packager fills in maintainer details, changelog, and
distro-specific adjustments.

What browse-sqlite3 Is
----------------------

browse-sqlite3 is a full-screen TUI browser for SQLite databases,
written in Python.  It provides table browsing, row navigation, and
field editing with vi-style keybindings and a Turbo Pascal-inspired
color scheme.  An optional C extension accelerates Unicode display-width
calculations.

Also installs a bs3 symlink as a short alias.

Dependencies
------------

Build-time:
  - Python 3.6+ with sqlite3 and curses modules
  - A C compiler (gcc, clang) for the optional _displaywidth extension
  - Python development headers (python3-dev / python3-devel) for the
    C extension

Runtime:
  - Python 3.6+ with sqlite3 and curses modules

How the Build Works
-------------------

1. ./configure detects Python, checks for sqlite3 and curses modules,
   and generates a Makefile from Makefile.in.
2. make compiles the optional C extension.
3. make install copies the script, C extension, manpage, and symlinks.

The configure script is hand-written POSIX shell -- no autoconf or
automake is required.  The build is simple enough that distro-specific
build systems can bypass configure entirely and install the files
directly.

What Gets Installed
-------------------

  $bindir/browse-sqlite3       Main program (Python script)
  $bindir/bs3                  Symlink to browse-sqlite3
  $mandir/man1/browse-sqlite3.1   Manpage
  $mandir/man1/bs3.1           Symlink to browse-sqlite3.1

The C extension (_displaywidth*.so) is loaded from the script's
directory or Python's import path at runtime.  If not found, the
program falls back to pure Python.

