Per-Distribution Notes
======================

RPM (Fedora / RHEL / CentOS)
-----------------------------

  Files:  dist/rpm/browse-sqlite3.spec

  Customize:
    - URL field (your fork or upstream)
    - %changelog section (add your name and entry)
    - Source0 URL if hosting your own tarball
    - Release tag / dist suffix as appropriate

  Build:  rpmbuild -ba dist/rpm/browse-sqlite3.spec
  Submit: Fedora -- follow the Fedora Package Review process
          EPEL -- follow EPEL packaging guidelines

Debian / Ubuntu
---------------

  Files:  dist/debian/

  Customize:
    - debian/changelog -- add your name, email, date, version
    - debian/control -- Maintainer field
    - Review debian/copyright for accuracy

  Build:  dpkg-buildpackage -us -uc
  Submit: File an ITP (Intent to Package) bug against wnpp

Arch Linux
----------

  Files:  dist/arch/PKGBUILD

  Customize:
    - Maintainer line at the top
    - source URL
    - sha256sums (run updpkgsums)

  Build:  makepkg -si
  Submit: Upload to AUR

Alpine Linux
------------

  Files:  dist/alpine/APKBUILD

  Customize:
    - Maintainer line at the top
    - source URL
    - sha512sums (run abuild checksum)

  Build:  abuild -r
  Submit: Open a merge request against aports.git

FreeBSD
-------

  Files:  dist/freebsd/

  Customize:
    - MAINTAINER email
    - distinfo -- fill in real SHA256 and SIZE from your tarball
    - Adjust MASTER_SITES if hosting the tarball yourself
    - Review pkg-plist after a test install

  Build:  make -C dist/freebsd install (in a ports tree)
  Submit: File a FreeBSD bug / send-pr with category "ports"

OpenBSD
-------

  Files:  dist/openbsd/

  Customize:
    - MAINTAINER email
    - Review pkg/PLIST after a test install

  Build:  make -C dist/openbsd install (in a ports tree)
  Submit: Send a diff to ports@openbsd.org

NetBSD
------

  Files:  dist/netbsd/

  Customize:
    - MAINTAINER email
    - distinfo -- fill in real hashes from your tarball (make distinfo)
    - MASTER_SITES if hosting the tarball yourself
    - Review PLIST after a test install

  Build:  bmake install (in a pkgsrc tree)
  Submit: Send a diff to pkgsrc-wip or the pkgsrc-changes list

Gentoo
------

  Files:  dist/gentoo/

  Customize:
    - metadata.xml -- maintainer name and email
    - Ebuild filename matches version (rename if bumping)
    - KEYWORDS -- adjust for your target architectures
    - SRC_URI -- point to your tarball or GitHub release

  Build:  ebuild dist/gentoo/browse-sqlite3-1.0.ebuild manifest && emerge browse-sqlite3
  Submit: File a bug at bugs.gentoo.org with category "Ebuild"
          or maintain via the GURU overlay

NixOS
-----

  Files:  dist/nixos/default.nix

  Customize:
    - fetchFromGitHub owner and hash (use nix-prefetch-url or nix flake)
    - meta.maintainers -- add your nixpkgs maintainer handle
    - Version string

  Build:  nix-build -E 'with import <nixpkgs> {}; callPackage ./dist/nixos/default.nix {}'
  Submit: Open a PR against nixpkgs adding the package under pkgs/

Slackware
---------

  Files:  dist/slackware/

  Customize:
    - browse-sqlite3.SlackBuild -- copyright header (your name)
    - browse-sqlite3.info -- MD5SUM, MAINTAINER, EMAIL
    - slack-desc -- homepage URL

  Build:  source browse-sqlite3.info && sh browse-sqlite3.SlackBuild
  Submit: Submit to SlackBuilds.org (SBo)
